This python script('package.py') installs some basic tools for a freshly installed UBUNTU desktop.

It installs git(version control system), unity tweak tool(used to customize your desktop), VLC media player, GIMP image editor, Shotcut video editor, Synaptic package manager, Sublime-text editor and Dropbox. 

Instructions for use :
-> Download the python script 'package.py'.
-> Run this script using 'python3 package.py' in your terminal.
-> That's it. You are good to go. All the packages will be installed automatically on your UBUNTU desktop. Just enter your password when prompted.

NOTE : This python script works only for UBUNTU desktops.
